{
  "message": "feat(overprompting): enhance 3D constraint visualization with HUD system\n\nUpgrades the overprompting article's constraint visualization with a more\nsophisticated heads-up display (HUD) system that better communicates how\nover-specification narrows the model's solution space.\n\nVisual improvements:\n- Added active protocols log showing constraint labels as they accumulate\n  (LIKENESS_LOCK_V2, POSE_MATCH_STRICT, CLOTHING_SYNC_ID, etc.)\n- Redesigned center warning indicator with scale animation\n- Imported RotateCcw icon for potential reset functionality\n- Structured HUD into top bar, center warning, and bottom system log\n- Protocol list shows last 3 active constraints with staggered animations\n- Empty state shows \"> System open...\" when no constraints active\n\nThe visualization now better demonstrates the article's thesis: that\nexcessive prompt constraints reduce output quality by eliminating too\nmuch of the creative search space, leaving the model unable to satisfy\nall requirements simultaneously.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
